<paragraph blockId="3.[164,779,716,1045]" pageId="3" pageNumber="700">
<emphasis box="[164,283,718,739]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="700">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Marine 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Shao &amp; Gong &amp; Li &amp; Lin &amp; Song" authorityYear="2010" box="[393,517,717,738]" class="Betaproteobacteria" family="Neisseriaceae" genus="Bergeriella" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Neisseriales" pageId="3" pageNumber="700" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,517,717,738]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="700">Bergeriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in vivo 80–120 ¥ 40– 60 Mm, body ellipsoidal to elongate ovoid, usually brownish in colour; yellow-brown cortical granules situated along cirral rows, and between dorsal kineties; 20–35 adoral membranelles; 6–13 frontal and 1–4 buccal cirri; midventral rows composed of 21–38 cirri, with 5–8 postoral ventral and 5–8 left ventral rows; 17–38 left and 19–38 right marginal cirri; one nonmigratory row consists of 16–32 cirri; normally 3 dorsal kineties; ~70–140 macronuclear nodules and 3–6 micronuclei.
</paragraph>
